WEBVTT

00:01:28.165 --> 00:01:32.934
which is the idea that technology
is fundamentally accelerating.

00:01:33.592 --> 00:01:34.742
Explain that.

00:01:35.472 --> 00:01:39.140
Ray Kurzweil: So, around 1981,

00:01:39.164 --> 00:01:42.773
I wanted to tie my inventions.

00:01:42.797 --> 00:01:45.070
The inventors whose names you recognize,

00:01:45.094 --> 00:01:47.680
like Thomas Edison or Larry Page,

00:01:47.704 --> 00:01:51.588
were in the right place
with the right idea at the right time.

00:01:51.965 --> 00:01:55.799
So I started studying technology trends.

00:01:55.823 --> 00:01:59.173
I didn't think I'd find anything
overly predictable.

00:01:59.197 --> 00:02:02.330
I started with the common wisdom,
'You cannot predict the future,"